02:12.318 --> 02:14.618
(Skype ringing)

02:14.620 --> 02:16.920
Sheldon, I don't think
you understand

02:16.922 --> 02:18.389
how being broken up works.

02:18.391 --> 02:20.658
The only way
I can sort through my feelings

02:20.660 --> 02:22.426
is if there is space between us.

02:22.428 --> 02:25.396
Every time I see you,
it re-traumatizes me.

02:25.398 --> 02:27.531
I go through the pain
all over again.

02:27.533 --> 02:29.700
Well, hello to you, too.

02:30.770 --> 02:32.469
What do you want?

02:32.471 --> 02:34.638
I understand
we're no longer a couple,

02:34.640 --> 02:38.208
but I would like to remind you
that we made a baby together.

02:40.413 --> 02:42.212
What baby?

02:42.214 --> 02:45.215
A precocious
little Internet show

02:45.217 --> 02:47.785
known as "Fun With Flags."

02:48.654 --> 02:50.287
I'm hanging up.

02:50.289 --> 02:52.423
Great. See you in
about half an hour.

02:52.425 --> 02:56.026
Sheldon, I am not doing
"Fun With Flags" with you.

02:56.028 --> 02:57.194
Why not?

02:57.196 --> 02:59.129
Because we're broken up.

02:59.131 --> 03:01.098
Sonny and Cher made it work.

03:01.100 --> 03:02.966
Their variety show
kept going

03:02.968 --> 03:04.034
long after the divorce,

03:04.036 --> 03:06.670
and here we are
still talking about them.

03:06.672 --> 03:09.873
No one's talking
about Sonny and Cher.

03:09.875 --> 03:11.909
You must be thinking
about Donny and Marie,

03:11.911 --> 03:14.545
'cause you and I are clearly
talking about Sonny and Cher.

03:15.981 --> 03:17.715
Sheldon, this has to stop.

03:17.717 --> 03:19.283
I know it's hard.

03:19.285 --> 03:20.984
It's hard for me, too.

03:20.986 --> 03:22.886
But I've seen
and talked to you more

03:22.888 --> 03:24.421
in the two days
we've been broken up

03:24.423 --> 03:27.124
than in the last two months
that we were together.

03:27.126 --> 03:28.792
Well, if you want
to see less of me,

03:28.794 --> 03:31.628
maybe we should go out again.

03:32.798 --> 03:34.965
I can't believe you made out
with Mandy Chao.

03:34.967 --> 03:37.000
Trust me,
I wish it never happened.

03:37.002 --> 03:39.403
And you knew about this
this whole time?

03:39.405 --> 03:40.604
I did.

03:40.606 --> 03:42.639
And you didn't think to tell me?

03:44.243 --> 03:46.577
Leonard asked me
to keep it to myself.

03:46.579 --> 03:48.912
Let's leave Leonard
out of this for the moment.

03:50.182 --> 03:52.716
This is about you and me.

03:54.086 --> 03:56.787
Wait, wait, wait, how is my
day-old marriage falling apart

03:56.789 --> 03:57.888
becoming about you two?

03:57.890 --> 03:59.056
Hang on.

03:59.058 --> 04:01.759
What do I need to do
to make you trust me?

04:01.761 --> 04:03.727
You think it's hard
having one wife,

04:03.729 --> 04:05.195
try having two.

04:06.298 --> 04:07.698
I bet you told Bernadette

04:07.700 --> 04:10.467
all about he was screwing around
with Mandy Chao.

04:10.469 --> 04:11.769
Oh, we didn't screw around.

04:11.771 --> 04:13.237
We just got drunk and made out.

04:13.239 --> 04:16.005
Whatever. It would have
been nice to hear it from you.

